&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;
&lt;div&gt;

&lt;!--TITRE DOCUMENT--&gt;


&lt;div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When we talk about complex IoT projects, ICT and business decision makers are looking for consulting and systems integration partners with dedicated expertise in specific areas to implement a full IoT solution. teknowlogy provides transparency for buyers to identify the best partner for their complex IoT projects. We have to consider that C&amp;amp;SI services for IoT solutions serve different use cases. For this reason, teknowlogy uses different RADAR segments, dedicated to specific uses cases, to evaluate the providers of C&amp;amp;SI for IoT solutions in Europe. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Among the five available analysis segments, this document focuses on Smart metering &amp;amp; services (CX &amp;amp; IoT) with the following definition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deployment of intelligent measuring systems for energy consumption (and generation in the case of renewable energies), allowing two-way communication and thus enabling real-time insight into power consumption (and generation) as well as new services such as differing tariffs, energy savings initiatives, smart home services, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;section class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h2 &gt;Use cases in the area of smart energy &amp;amp; resources&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This part represents a list of relevant use cases in this context. The list is not exclusive and will be revised frequently. The main uses cases are as following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 &gt;Smart grids/intelligent network management (IoT)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provision, management and operation of intelligent energy transmission networks able to dynamically manage decentralized energy usage over time and space according to supply and demand. Includes advanced diagnostic features to analyze in real time the state of the network, enabling higher efficiency of the overall grid operation. Digital technologies and platforms allow a consolidated view of the grid, combining and analyzing asset information, geographical location, financial data, weather info, etc. This enables complex analyses that improve transmission and distribution network management, asset management (thus reducing asset risks) and allows for load balancing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 &gt;Intelligent operation/automation &amp;amp; predictive maintenance (IoT)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The use of sensors and connectivity modules (RFID, WiFi, sensors, Bluetooth, etc.) as well as analytics to identify malfunctions and optimize maintenance by improving upfront scheduling of maintenance services and asset optimization.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 &gt;Digital mining &amp;amp; exploration (IoT)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use of analytics, automation, IoT, cloud, mobile and collaboration in mining &amp;amp; exploration to improve operating efficiency, develop more accurate and agile exploration/transportation planning (from “pit to port”) and collaborate more effectively with business partners throughout the value chain.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 &gt;Virtual power plants (IoT)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deployment of advanced software/platforms/systems to connect distributed energy generators and energy storage units to become VPPs. Digital technologies are needed for optimization, control and secure communication purposes to ensure effective plant management and thus reliable power supply.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;

&lt;section class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h2 &gt;Selection of providers&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Providers are selected and invited according to the following criteria: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul &gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Size of revenues&lt;/strong&gt; in the segment to be analyzed in the specified region &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“Relevance”&lt;/strong&gt;: Even providers that do not belong to the top-selling providers in the segment to be analyzed are considered, if teknowlogy classifies them as relevant for potential customers, for instance due to an innovative offering, strong growth, or a compelling vision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is no differentiation as to whether the providers are customers of teknowlogy – neither in the selection of the providers to be positioned, nor in the actual evaluation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The decision as to which providers are considered in the teknowlogy INNOVATION RADAR analysis is entirely up to teknowlogy. Providers do not have any direct influence on this decision. &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h3 &gt;Providers positioned in the segment of C&amp;amp;SI for IoT solutions for smart energy &amp;amp; resources&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul &gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABB&lt;/strong&gt; is a Swedish-Swiss multinational corporation headquartered in Zurich, Switzerland, and operating mainly in robotics, power, heavy electrical equipment and automation technology. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accenture&lt;/strong&gt; has become a major provider of business and IT consulting Accenture positions itself as an end-to-end service provider to support its customers in their digital transformation by&quot;helping organizations maximize their performance and achieve their vision&quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Atos&lt;/strong&gt; is a €12 billion revenue company with 100,000 employees in 72 countries. Atos conducts business through three service lines: consulting, systems integration and managed operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BearingPoint&lt;/strong&gt; is a multinational management and technology consulting firm headquartered in Amsterdam, the Netherlands. It has operations in 35 countries with around 3,901 employees and is one of the largest management consultancies in Europe with an annual revenue. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Capgemini&lt;/strong&gt; is a France-based company and offers business consulting, functional &amp;amp; IT-oriented consulting, integration and development, outsourcing and BPO services in the country, both in the application and infrastructure fields.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CGI&lt;/strong&gt; is a Canadian IT consulting, systems integration, outsourcing and solutions company founded in 1976. Since the acquisition of Logica in 2012, CGI is the fifth-largest independent business processes and IT services provider in the world with approximately 70,000 members (the internal word for employees) across 40 countries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cognizant&lt;/strong&gt; started out in 1994 as the technology arm of The Dun &amp;amp; Bradstreet Corporation. Today, its business units are aligned with digital solutions and services. The company is headquartered in Teaneck, New Jersey, and employs 260,200 people worldwide.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Deloitte&lt;/strong&gt; company network is made up of independent firms, owned and managed locally, members of global accounting powerhouse Deloitte Touche Tohmatsu Limited (DTTL). Deloitte's business is focused on five core areas: audit, consulting, financial advisory, enterprise risk services and tax &amp;amp; legal. The company has 263,900 employees and generated an annual revenue of USD 38.8 billion in 2017.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Device Insight&lt;/strong&gt;, founded in 2003, is a Germany-based, specialized provider of Internet of Things platforms. The company’s services range from business case analysis to implementation and secure IT operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DXC Technology&lt;/strong&gt; a technology service provider, was formed in 2017 by the merger of Computer Sciences Corporation (CSC) and the Enterprise Services business of Hewlett Packard Enterprise (formerly Electronic Data Systems). DXC provides information technology and consulting services to businesses and governments. The company operates in more than 70 countries and has 155,000 employees. USD 25 billion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EY (formerly Ernst &amp;amp; Young)&lt;/strong&gt; is a multinational professional services company headquartered in London, UK, providing assurance, tax, consulting and advisory services. It is one of the largest professional services firms in the world and operates as a network of member companies, which are separate legal entities in the individual countries. The company employs 247,570 people in around 150 countries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IBM&lt;/strong&gt; is a global technology company, founded in 1911, that provides hardware, software, cloud-based services and cognitive computing. It is one of the world's largest employers, with over 380,000 employees in over 170 countries. &lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Siemens AG&lt;/strong&gt;, founded in 1847, is a German electronics and electrical engineering company. The company’s portfolio ranges from products and services for industry automation and drives to transportation systems, Siemens building technologies, OSRAM lighting solutions, and mobility solutions and services, plus system integration and solutions for the power plant business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sopra Steria&lt;/strong&gt; arose from the 2014 merger of two French digital services companies, Sopra and Steria, founded in 1968 and 1969, respectively. The group is active in the field of digital transformation, supporting customers from both the services and the solutions side. The company has 40,000 employees.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) &lt;/strong&gt; was established in 1968 as the IT subsidiary of Tata Sons Limited. TCS is one of the leading global IT services providers based in India, with a global workforce of over 387,000 employees. Today, TCS positions itself as an end-to-end service provider to support its customers in their digital transformation by&quot;helping clients create the future”.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wipro Limited&lt;/strong&gt; (formerly Western India Products Limited) is an Indian multinational provider of IT services, consulting and outsourcing services. Wipro is now a truly global corporation with operations in over 70 countries and more than 170,000 employees. IT services are the biggest part of its business by far. &lt;/li&gt;
