&lt;h3 &gt;teknowlogy INNOVATION RADAR evaluation method&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Concept and methodology of the teknowlogy INNOVATION RADAR are similar to those of the traditional teknowlogy RADAR. While the traditional teknowlogy RADAR focuses on mature services segments, the teknowlogy INNOVATION RADAR, however, positions providers in rather new and innovative service segments. Thus the focus of the evaluation is rather on the portfolio, vision, investment and capabilities than on existing references, projects and resources.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-weight-bold&quot;&gt;For the teknowlogy INNOVATION RADAR the following applies: The closer a company is to the top right corner, the closer they are to meeting customers’ requirements!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&quot;mtk-figure&quot;&gt;
&lt;figcaption class=&quot;mtk-figure-title&quot;&gt;Clusters and sub-clusters of the teknowlogy INNOVATION RADAR by which providers are evaluated&lt;/figcaption&gt;
   &lt;div class=&quot;mtk-figure-img&quot;&gt;
  &lt;a class=&quot;img-lightbox&quot;  style=&quot;display:block;text-align:center&quot;&gt;
